article.description: Justyna Podziemska scored 19 points to lead Wyoming (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) over Texas Christian 62-45 Saturday.
article.headline: Late run gives Wyoming win over TCU
article.linkText: Late run gives Wyoming win over TCU
article.story:
LARAMIE, Wyo. (AP) -- Justyna Podziemska scored 19 points to lead Wyoming (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) over Texas Christian 62-45 Saturday.

Elizabeth Dissen added 10 points for the Cowgirls (14-1, 2-0 Mountain West Conference) on 5-of-5 shooting and Aubrey Vandiver had eight rebounds.

Adrianne Ross and Lori Butler-Rayford scored nine points apiece for the Lady Frogs (8-8, 1-1).

Wyoming opened up a 35-25 lead after Podziemska hit her second 3-pointer with 13:22 remaining in the game.

A 3 from Helena Sverrisdottir with 7:17 to go pulled TCU within 43-37, but Wyoming scored 19 of the final 27 points in the game to seal the win.

Wyoming went on a 10-2 run midway through the first half to take a 14-7 lead. The Lady Frogs tied the score at 18 with 2:59 remaining, but the Cowgirls went on a 5-0 run to take a 23-18 lead into the break.
